            . On the 15th of November, about nine o'clock at night, and saw a hat snatched from the door. I ran out, and saw the prisoner running along Whitechapel with it in his hand; I pursued him up a court, and secured him, but he had by that time made away with it; I have not found it since; it was tied by a string, which he cut.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. My mother sent me to the court for some dirty linen; the gentleman looked at me, went away for a minute, then returned and took me.</p>
               <p>MR. SALT. It is false.</p>
